### ============================================================
### INSTRUMENT: Thomas-Kilmann Conflict Mode Instrument (TKI)
### Developer: Kenneth Thomas & Ralph Kilmann (1974; revised 2007)
### Format: 30 forced-choice item pairs | Ipsative scoring
### Subscales: competing, collaborating, compromising, avoiding, accommodating
### Level: Individual
### Admin time: 15–20 minutes
### ============================================================
###
### ⚠ NEW SCHEMA REQUIREMENTS FOR THIS INSTRUMENT:
###
###   "type": "forced_choice"
###     A new question type where the respondent picks one of exactly
###     two statements (A or B). Neither is "correct" — both are
###     socially desirable to prevent acquiescence bias.
###
###   "options": [ { "value": "A", "text": "...", "subscale": "..." },
###                { "value": "B", "text": "...", "subscale": "..." } ]
###     Each forced-choice pair maps each option to a different subscale.
###     The scoring engine increments the chosen subscale's raw score.
###
###   "pair_id": integer
###     Sequential pair number (1–30). Used by the scoring engine to
###     reconstruct the full 5×6 scoring matrix.
###
###   "scoring": { "method": "ipsative" }
###     Signals that scores are relative (sum = 30 across all subscales),
###     not absolute. Prevents cross-person parametric comparison.
###
###   "scale_descriptor": "forced_choice_dyad"
###     Indicates no Likert scale is used; UI renders two radio options.
###
### ============================================================

POST http://localhost:3030/api/surveys/templates
Content-Type: application/json
